== Balsamic Parsley Salsa ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch 
of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the potato.

Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). 
Halve the @red chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped) 
lengthways, deseed and finely chop.

Pop the parsley and the chilli in a #small bowl{} with the @balsamic vinegar{} 
and @olive oil{} and mix together. This is your salsa!

== Sausage Pie ==

Slice open the @pork sausage meat{500%g}, remove the meat and discard the skin.

Add the @potatoes{3%large}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks) to your 
pan of boiling water and simmer until cooked, ~{20%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Peel the @carrot{1}(peeled, halved lengthways and sliced into thin half moons) 
and remove the top and bottom.

Chop the large @broccoli{1%head}(chopped into florets).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, 
add the sausage meat. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks and fry 
until brown, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the carrot to the pan, stir and cook until softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{} and stir in the 
@beef stock pot{1} (make sure it's dissolved).

Pour in the @water{}.

Stir the sausage mixture well, bring to the boil, then turn the heat to medium. 
Simmer until the carrot is cooked and the mixture is thick and tomatoey, 
~{20%minutes}.

When the potato is cooked, drain in a #colander{}, then return it to the pan. 
Add the @butter{} and some @black pepper{}. Mash together with a #potato masher{}. 
Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

When the sausage mixture is cooked, taste and add salt and pepper if necessary. 
Pour it into your #ovenproof dish{} and spread evenly across the base.

Add spoonfuls of mashed potato on top and spread to cover the sausage mixture.

Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{100%g}. Pop the dish on the 
top shelf of your oven to cook until the cheese is browned, 
~{15-20%minutes}.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, spread the @tenderstem® broccoli{200%g} on one side of a 
#baking tray{} and the broccoli florets on the other side.

Drizzle with a splash of @olive oil{} and add a pinch of @salt{} and 
@black pepper{}.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Spoon the sausage pie into #bowls{}. Serve the kids the broccoli florets. Drizzle 
the balsamic parsley salsa over the tenderstem® broccoli for the adults and 
serve the adults too. Enjoy!